<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/46667560-robert-irish"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1493082399i/46667560._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/46667560-robert-irish">Robert Irish</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">In time sequence Skin of a Lion comes before English Patient, so if one wants to get the characters in sequence, you would start with Skin of a Lion, <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">In time sequence Skin of a Lion comes before English Patient, so if one wants to get the characters in sequence, you would start with Skin of a Lion, but it doesn't matter. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
